The reads in the FASTQ files generated above were mapped onto the reference human genome (hg19) using the BWA [48] memory module with the parameter –T 19. CIRI [12, 13] (version 2.0.6) was used to detect putative circRNAs with the parameter −0 –A using the gene annotation file (GENCODE v19, http://www.gencodegenes.org) from each mapped file. CIRI calculates the number of circular junction counts and the circular ratio using the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
